2009-03-17  Vincent Untz  <vuntz@mate.org>

	* configure.in: post-release bump to 2.26.1

==================== 2.26.0 ====================

2009-03-17  Vincent Untz  <vuntz@mate.org>

	* NEWS:
	* configure.in: version 2.26.0

2009-01-31  Vincent Untz  <vuntz@mate.org>

	* configure.in: post-release bump to 2.25.91

==================== 2.25.90 ====================

2009-01-31  Vincent Untz  <vuntz@mate.org>

	* configure.in:
	* NEWS: version 2.25.90

2008-12-07  Cosimo Cecchi  <cosimoc@mate.org>

	* demos/dash-demo.c:
	* tests/test-libglade-canvas.c:
	Use single GTK+ includes also for tests and demos.
	Thanks to Przemysław Grzegorczyk (#563566).

2008-10-19  Cosimo Cecchi  <cosimoc@mate.org>

	* libmatecanvas/mate-canvas-bpath.c:
	* libmatecanvas/mate-canvas-clipgroup.c:
	* libmatecanvas/mate-canvas-shape.c:
	More GTK+ single header include fixage.

2008-10-18  Cosimo Cecchi  <cosimoc@mate.org>

	* configure.in:
	* libmatecanvas/Makefile.am:
	* libmatecanvas/gailcanvas.h:
	* libmatecanvas/mate-canvas-pixbuf.c:
	* libmatecanvas/mate-canvas-rich-text.c:
	* libmatecanvas/mate-canvas-rich-text.h:
	* libmatecanvas/mate-canvas.c:
	* libmatecanvas/mate-canvas.h:
	Use and enforce single GTK+ includes.

2008-09-01  Stefan Kost  <ensonic@users.sf.net>

	* libmatecanvas/mate-canvas-bpath.h:
	* libmatecanvas/mate-canvas-clipgroup.h:
	* libmatecanvas/mate-canvas-line.h:
	* libmatecanvas/mate-canvas-pixbuf.h:
	* libmatecanvas/mate-canvas-polygon.h:
	* libmatecanvas/mate-canvas-rect-ellipse.h:
	* libmatecanvas/mate-canvas-rich-text.h:
	* libmatecanvas/mate-canvas-shape.h:
	* libmatecanvas/mate-canvas-text.h:
	* libmatecanvas/mate-canvas-widget.h:
	* libmatecanvas/mate-canvas.h:
	  Do not use deprecated GTK_OBJECT macros. This helps to build apps with
	  deprecation warnings when using libmatecanvas.

2008-08-12  Sven Herzberg  <sven@imendio.com>

	Bug 469482 – need to register gailcanvas into a11y type system

	* libmatecanvas/gailcanvas.c,
	* libmatecanvas/gailcanvas.h,
	* libmatecanvas/mate-canvas.c: properly initialize gail canvas

2008-03-05  Vincent Untz  <vuntz@mate.org>

	* configure.in: bump version to 2.21.92, even if nothing was released.
	This is need to get mate-sharp compile some mate features (it
	checks for a version >= 2.20.x) in jhbuild.

2008-01-22  Tor Lillqvist  <tml@novell.com>

	* libmatecanvas-zip.in: Look for catalogs in share/locale first,
	as that is where they will end up with a properly built GNU
	gettext.

2007-11-05  Federico Mena Quintero  <federico@novell.com>

	Fix these bugs:
	http://bugzilla.mate.org/show_bug.cgi?id=493808
	https://bugzilla.novell.com/show_bug.cgi?id=336941

	* libmatecanvas/mate-canvas.c (paint): Oops, use the correct
	visible rectangle; we forgot to take the zoom_{x,y}ofs into
	account.  Also, take those offsets into account when generating
	the actual rectangle to be added to the GdkRegion.

2007-08-29  Sven Herzberg  <herzi@mate-de.org>

	* libmatecanvas/gailcanvas.c: fix compilation with gcc 2.x (Patch by
	Jens Granseur, fixes #455662)

2007-08-22  Federico Mena Quintero  <federico@novell.com>

	Avoid tearing while repainting.

	* libmatecanvas/mate-canvas.c (REDRAW_QUANTUM_SIZE): Renamed
	from IMAGE_{WIDTH, HEIGHT}; use a single value.
	(IMAGE_WIDTH_AA, IMAGE_HEIGHT_AA): Removed.
	(paint): Don't use different redraw quantum sizes for the
	antialiased and non-antialiased case.  Extract big rectangles from
	the microtile array, turn them into a GdkRegion, and *then* expose
	with that region, so that we can repaint without tearing.
	(mate_canvas_paint_rect): Don't use different redraw quantum
	sizes for the antialiased and non-antialiased case.
	(mate_canvas_paint_rect): Don't tile the area to paint; instead, draw 
	the complete rectangle in one pass.  The callers already took care of 
	generating appropriate rectangles for us.

============================= 2.19.2 ========================

2007-07-26  Sven Herzberg  <herzi@mate-de.org>

	* libmatecanvas/mate-canvas.c: don't store the focused item in the
	data section of the canvas widget, but in a GObject property of it
	(Patch by Li Yuan, fixes 363103)

============================= 2.19.1 ========================

2007-07-11  Sven Herzberg  <herzi@mate-de.org>

	* configure.ac,
	* ChangeLog,
	* NEWS,
	* po/ChangeLog: update files for 2.19.1

2007-07-11  Sven Herzberg  <herzi@mate-de.org>

	* libmatecanvas/libmatecanvas-2.0.pc.in: depend on the right gail.pc
	file

============================= 2.19.0 ========================

2007-07-10  Sven Herzberg  <herzi@mate-de.org>

	* configure.ac,
	* ChangeLog,
	* po/ChangeLog: update files for 2.19.0

2007-06-25  Sven Herzberg  <herzi@mate-de.org>

	Roll ATK support for MateCanvas into libmatecanvas,
	formerly it was in libgail. Patch by Bill Haneman.
	See bug #363103.

	* configure.in:
	Depend on libgail explicitly, since the ATK support for
	mate-canvas uses some libgail-util API.

	* libmatecanvas/mate-canvas.c:
	(mate_canvas_init): Register the gail_canvas factory types
	with ATK when MateCanvas is first used.

	* libmatevanvas/gailcanvas.[ch]: New, bootstraps
	ATK support for MateCanvas instances and provides
	ATK implementations for MateCanvas.

	* libmatevanvas/gailcanvasitem.[ch]: New, ATK support
	for generic canvas items.

	* libmatevanvas/gailcanvaswidget.[ch]: New, ATK support
	for canvas internal widgets.
	
	* libmatevanvas/gailcanvastext.[ch]: New, ATK support
	for canvas text objects.	

	* libmatevanvas/gailcanvas*factory.[ch]: New,
	factories for creating the above ATK peers on demand,
	that is, when gtk_widget_get_accessible() is called
	on the corresponding MateCanvas instances or their
	sub-parts.

2007-06-04  Sven Herzberg  <herzi@mate-de.org>

	Patch from Li Yuan:

	* libmatecanvas/mate-canvas.c: (mate_canvas_item_grab_focus):
	store the focused item in the "focused_item" object data of the canvas
	(required for gail to drop the dependency on libmatecanvas)

2007-05-24  Sven Herzberg  <herzi@mate-de.org>

	Reverting the gail canvas commit to not introduce a circular
	dependency.

2007-05-23  Sven Herzberg  <herzi@mate-de.org>

	Roll ATK support for MateCanvas into libmatecanvas,
	formerly it was in libgail. Patch by Bill Haneman.
	See bug #363103.

	* configure.in:
	Depend on libgail explicitly, since the ATK support for
	mate-canvas uses some libgail-util API.
	
	* libmatecanvas/mate-canvas.c:
	(mate_canvas_init): Register the gail_canvas factory types
	with ATK when MateCanvas is first used.

	* libmatevanvas/gailcanvas.[ch]: New, bootstraps 
	ATK support for MateCanvas instances and provides
	ATK implementations for MateCanvas.

	* libmatevanvas/gailcanvasitem.[ch]: New, ATK support
	for generic canvas items.
	
	* libmatevanvas/gailcanvaswidget.[ch]: New, ATK support
	for canvas internal widgets.
	
	* libmatevanvas/gailcanvastext.[ch]: New, ATK support 
	for canvas text objects.	
	
	* libmatevanvas/gailcanvas*factory.[ch]: New,
	factories for creating the above ATK peers on demand,
	that is, when gtk_widget_get_accessible() is called
	on the corresponding MateCanvas instances or their
	sub-parts.

============================= 2.14.1 ========================

2006-11-27  Sven Herzberg  <herzi@mate-de.org>

	* docs/reference/tmpl/mate-canvas.sgml: commiting documentation about
	removing canvas items

2006-11-22  Sven Herzberg  <herzi@mate-de.org>

	* libmatecanvas/mate-canvas-text.c: improved the calculation of the
	bounding box. Fixes bug #155317 (Based on a patch from Roderich
	Schupp)

2006-11-22  Sven Herzberg  <herzi@mate-de.org>

	* docs/reference/tmpl/mate-canvas-text.sgml,
	* libmatecanvas/mate-canvas-text.c: added some documentation about
	the fact that MateCanvasText doesn't zoom. Closes bug #154679
	(Pointed out by Stefan Kost)

2006-11-18  Sven Herzberg  <herzi@mate-de.org>

	* libmatecanvas/mate-canvas.c: added documentation about how to pass
	construct parameters to MateCanvasItem implementations. Closes bug
	#156165 (Pointed out by Stefan Kost)

2006-11-17  Sven Herzberg  <herzi@mate-de.org>

	* src/mate-canvas-shape.c: changed the get_property() implementation
	for "dash" to return something useful (ArtVpathDash*) and also to be
	consistent with set_property() ('though tis code really sucks as we
	should really use GParamSpecBoxed instead). Closes bug #153585
	(Patch by Peter G. Baum)

2006-11-14  Sven Herzberg  <herzi@mate-de.org>

	* configure.in: depend on pkg-config 0.18
	* libmatecanvas/libmatecanvas-2.0.pc.in: move pango dependencies to
	Requires.private. Closes bug #352196 (Bug reported by Samuel Thibault)

2006-11-12  Sven Herzberg  <herzi@mate-de.org>

	* demos/Makefile.am: build dash demo
	* demos/dash-demo.c: a demo to demonstrate the dash property
	* libmatecanvas/mate-canvas-shape.c: don't allocate too much memory.
	Closes bug #153583 (Patch from Peter G. Baum)

2006-11-10  Kjartan Maraas  <kmaraas@mate.org>

	* NEWS: Update some.
	* libmatecanvas/mate-canvas-text.h: Convert to UTF-8.
	Noticed by Danny Milo. Closes bug #164327.

2006-11-10  Kjartan Maraas  <kmaraas@mate.org>

	* libmatecanvas/mate-canvas-shape.c: (gcbp_ensure_mask):
	Fix a typo in a g_object_set_data call. Reported by elubarsky at
	gmail com. Closes bug #355580.

2006-07-11  Sven Herzberg  <herzi@mate-de.org>

	* libmatecanvas/mate-canvas.c: allow group->destroy() to modify
	group->item_list without unleashing hell (developed with Tim Janik)

2006-06-17  Kjartan Maraas  <kmaraas@mate.org>

	* .cvsignore:
	* Makefile.am:
	* configure.in: Patch from Przemysław Grzegorczyk to
	use po/LINGUAS. Closes bug #338549.

2006-04-18  Kjartan Maraas  <kmaraas@mate.org>

	* configure.in: Remove obsolete entry for no_NO
	* po/no.po: And the translation.

Tue Apr 11 16:46:20 2006  Tim Janik  <timj@gtk.org>

	* libmatecanvas/mate-canvas.c:
	mate_canvas_set_pixels_per_unit():
	scroll_to(): applied a patch from Sven Herzberg to check hadjustment
	and vadjustment for NULL. the rationale is provided in #305941.

