2002-01-17  Lauris Kaplinski  <lauris@ximian.com>

	* libmatecanvas/mate-canvas.c (mate_canvas_item_invoke_update): Clean up code a bit,
	mostly to help myself to keep track of affine transformations
	(mate_canvas_item_invoke_point): Ditto
	(mate_canvas_item_affine_relative): Ditto
	(mate_canvas_item_affine_absolute): Ditto
	(do_update): Start updating root with w2c affine
	(scroll_to): Schedule widget redraw if scroll ofsets change - this is not
	the best approach, but IMHO not too bad either, as this can happen only
	if either canvas size or widget size change - not for normal scrolling

2002-01-16  Lauris Kaplinski  <lauris@ximian.com>

	* libmatecanvas/mate-canvas-shape.c (mate_canvas_shape_update): Check for NULL path,
	kill warning by path def
	(mate_canvas_shape_bounds): Ditto

	* libmatecanvas/mate-canvas.c (mate_canvas_expose): Emit parent class expose event here,
	so widget items get drawn

	* libmatecanvas/mate-canvas-widget.c (mate_canvas_widget_render): Comment everything out,
	or we are creating endless stream of exposes
	(mate_canvas_widget_draw): Ditto

	* libmatecanvas/mate-canvas-util.c (mate_canvas_update_svp): Clean it up, use rect
	coverage for small SVP-s (is much faster).

2002-01-15  Lauris Kaplinski  <lauris@ximian.com>

	* libmatecanvas/mate-canvas-bpath.c (mate_canvas_bpath_set_property): Use new
	signature for setting path to avoid warning

