2001-08-14  Martin Baulig  <baulig@suse.de>

	Released libmatecanvas 1.102.0 "Roswell".

	* configure.in: Bumped version number to 1.102.0.

2001-08-14  Darin Adler  <darin@bentspoon.com>

	Roll in some more desirable fixes from the stable branch.

	2001-02-11  Rusty Conover  <rconover@zootweb.com>

	* mate-canvas-line.c (mate_canvas_line_set_arg): Added fix for
	when the color of a line changes the SVP's of the arrowheads also
	change color.  They didn't change color before.

	2000-05-01  Iain Holmes  <ih@csd.abdn.ac.uk>

	* mate-canvas-widget.c (mate_canvas_widget_render)
	(mate_canvas_widget_draw): New functions to queue a widget redraw
	when the item is redrawn.
	(mate_canvas_widget_class_init): Connect the render and draw
	functions to the item.

	2000-02-15  Federico Mena Quintero  <federico@helixcode.com>

	* mate-canvas-line.c (get_points): New function to copy the list
	of the line's points without the endpoint adjustments for
	arrowheads.  Based on a patch by Rusty Conover <rconover@zootweb.com>.
	(mate_canvas_line_get_arg): Use get_points().

2001-08-13  Darin Adler  <darin@bentspoon.com>

	Roll in some desirable fixes from the stable branch:

	2000-05-05  Miguel de Icaza  <miguel@helixcode.com>

	* libmatecanvas/mate-canvas.c (mate_canvas_new_aa): New policy.  Most of the
	problems on the mate-canvas-aa can be fixed.  So instead of
	scaring off people with the AA canvas, we will address their needs
	as the bug reports arrive.  

	Discussed this with Federico today.
	
	2000-04-23  Iain Holmes  <ih@csd.abdn.ac.uk>

	* libmatecanvas/mate-canvas.c (item_post_create_setup): Redraw +1 pixel on both
	x and y axis.
	(redraw_if_visible): Same
	(mate_canvas_item_show): Same
	(mate_canvas_item_hide): Same

	2000-02-15  Federico Mena Quintero  <federico@helixcode.com>

	* libmatecanvas/mate-canvas.c (uta_union_clip): New function to create the
	union of two microtile arrays while clipping the result to a given
	rectangle.  This is based on a wonderful problem analysis and
	patch by Michael Meeks <michael@helixcode.com>.  He deserves a
	beer.
	(mate_canvas_request_redraw_uta): Use uta_union_clip().  Now we
	only queue redraws of microtile arrays clipped against the canvas
	visible area.  This *is* the right thing to do.
	(mate_canvas_set_pixels_per_unit): No longer clear the redraw
	area before scrolling/thawing.  This hack can rest in peace now.

	2000-02-15  Christopher James Lahey  <clahey@helixcode.com>

	* libmatecanvas/mate-canvas.c (emit_event): Fixed a bug where GDK_FOCUS_CHANGE
	events weren't being dispatched properly.

	2000-01-06  Federico Mena Quintero  <federico@helixcode.com>

	* libmatecanvas/mate-canvas.c (mate_canvas_group_bounds): Do update the child
	pointer when we walk the list.  Thanks to Richard Hult for
	pointing this out.

2001-08-13  Darin Adler  <darin@bentspoon.com>

	* libmatecanvas/mate-canvas.h:
	* libmatecanvas/mate-canvas.c: (mate_canvas_item_grab):
	Use GDK's grab constants, not the raw ones from X.

2001-08-13  Darin Adler  <darin@bentspoon.com>

	* libmatecanvas/Makefile.am: Generate marshal files.
	* libmatecanvas/.cvsignore: Ignore generated marshal files.
	* libmatecanvas/mate-canvas-marshal.list: New file with the one marshal we need.
	
	* libmatecanvas/mate-canvas.h: Add mate_canvas_set_dither and
	mate_canvas_get_dither from the stable branch. Add signals to
	allow control of background. Remove obsolete
	mate_canvas_group_child_bounds.
	* libmatecanvas/mate-canvas.c: Remove obsolete mate_canvas_group_child_bounds.
	(mate_canvas_class_init): Set up new signals.
	(mate_canvas_init): Set up default dither.
	(paint): Use the new render_background and draw_background signals
	to paint the background.
	(mate_canvas_draw_background): New default handler for
	draw_background signal.
	(mate_canvas_set_dither), (mate_canvas_get_dither): Added.

	* libmatecanvas/mate-canvas-line.c: (mate_canvas_line_set_property),
	(mate_canvas_line_update): Removed OLD_XFORM code.
	
	* libmatecanvas/mate-canvas-rich-text.c: Fix a lot of warnings.
	(mate_canvas_rich_text_render): Do a g_warning instead of just
	quietly not drawing anything for the antialiased case.
	
	* libmatecanvas/mate-canvas-text.c: (recalc_bounds): Remove use of obsolete
	mate_canvas_group_child_bounds.
	* libmatecanvas/mate-canvas-widget.c: (recalc_bounds): Remove use of obsolete
	mate_canvas_group_child_bounds.

